<p><strong>State-of-the-Art methods of Re-identification:</strong><br />
Current methods of player re-identification mainly focus on two ways - one is to get high quality discriminative features 
and other is to define the distance metric which can be used as a loss for learning task effectively. I will talk here 
about the prior as it aligned with the requirements of the class. While learning the features from the images, it is important to 
work on relatively similar scale of the images. In more open-world settings, distance of objects from the camera is different, 
and so ae there sizes in the image; although to some extent it is taken care by cropping the image and resizing the images to same size, 
it is important to construct features from different scales in an image. One of such methods is from the authors of OsNET<a class="citation" href="#zhou2019osnet">(Zhou et al., 2019)</a>.<br />
OsNET was also SOTA method in SoccerNet baselines which gave the best results.</p>

